I came in here this afternoon because my body was craving for some real healthy food. I had been to a previous location, but zi still wasn't sure about what to order.  After checking the menu, I decided to go for the Buffalo Chicken Salad. This thing included blackened chicken, romaine lettuce, tomatoes, and a bunch of other ingredients that are too numerous to mention here. They prepared the salad in under one minute, and I quickly realized that there was nowhere to sit. I mean literally nowhere to sit. Some of the other restaurants close by at least had a couple of tables set-up outside. Not this place. They had a single table with a single chair situated near the front entrance.  It wasn't a huge deal, and I decided to just bring the food to my apartment and eat it there. I'm used to eating at home anyway. The salad had a medoly of different flavors, and my body was loving me for making the right decision!

What's healthy, fast and tasty? This place for sure. Whenever I get the craving for some extra vitamins and minerals I come to this establishment because I know the salads and warm bowls won't let me down. Chock full of kale and healthy fats, I've never been disappointed by a bowl. Perhaps at times even delaighted by some of the ingredients. (Basil in the Miso Warm Bowl for example). You even get to adjust how much sugar you want in your drink with this liquid syrup on the side. Ingredients are always tasty and fresh. You can never go wrong with dressings. Instead of croutons they serve bread. The bread is still good but can be dry sometimes and is optional. My go to favorites are the Harvest Bowl and Miso Bowl. Sweetgreen is a reliable fast healthy option. I enjoy that they don't have too many overwhelming options. My only gripe is that their a bit pricey but you get what you pay for in terms of quality of food (but not quantity of protein portion).

No heavy sodas! 🥰 When I was done, I was quite content-- well into the latter dinner hours. I will most certainly return! 👍👍

I have been going to Sweetgreen for many years. I was so in love with their salads that I was asked to be part of a program for their marketing team to try out a salad each month (they’d pay me) and I’d review it). So it is safe to say that I have a lot of love for this restaurant. This was my first time at this particular Sweetgreen, however. I went around noon on a weekday and it wasn’t too busy. The person who made my salad wasn’t particularly friendly (didn’t smile much). I asked for a guacamole greens no onion. They are supposed to ask if I wanted to substitute anything for onion, he didn’t. He barely put any mesclun in the bowl. Now, this is my issue with the new bowls: they barely fill them up. I get a significant less amount of salad with them. That’s pretty bogus since I’m paying close to $10 a salad. I asked for more lettuce politely and he rolled his eyes and mumbled under his breath. I asked for medium dressing, he gave me light. I then asked for dressing on the side, since I felt like I was bothering him asking for more. Overall, not a great experience. Felt like they were just trying to push you out and not much attention given to the customers.

This was my first time and probably my last. The food was excellent. Everything was fresh, tasty,  and hit the spot. The staff ... not so much.  The selection is be a bit overwhelming. The young lady behind the counter was no help. She gave me this look like I was an idiot because I wanted to take a moment to see all of choices. When I was done she barked to the cashier what I had ordered, rolled her eyes and walked away. The cashier promptly gave a price then sighed when I asked if I could also have a drink.  No one was in line behind me and they had a total of four people in the entire establishment. Had I been there when they were busy God only knows what kind of scouring look I would have gotten. In summary,  food is great, service is awful.

Excellent Customer Service. Denis, possibly a manger if not he should be was at check out. I went to pay and he informed me it was credit only, as I went to give cash for the order. He said politely and very happily "your meal is on me today" I tried to give him the cash directly and he said "no thank you" In a city at times where you just can shake your head here is a person and a place where you can shake thier hand! Hats off to you Denis and a true sincere THANK YOU , A true gentleman and world class customer service at it's finest in a service based restaurant industry.

Absolutely delicious food. I was just passing through, but if I lived in the city I'd eat here constantly. Great staff who explained vegan options, and they let me freely sub two veggies in my bowl since I didn't want the feta that the order normally came with. They even gave me a bowl of falafel and hummus for an extra couple of bucks. Everything was very clean and all the food was fresh. Loved the matcha Fresca. Plus it's just a couple doors down from a Whole Foods if you have room for some sweet treats afterwards!

What a little gem! It can be hard to find GOOD salads that are also actually healthy.  If you want superfoods,  or light,  HOUSEmade dressing,  this is your jam.  I also love how they list their suppliers on a chalkboard.  The drinks are really tasty as well,  and the staff are always really great. I mean great. Finding employees that give a crap in DC is not easy. I walk around getting mumbled at by people who act like I've just asked them to climb everest when i ask them about a menu item or where something is. Take Whole  Foods across the street...horrible staff.  Now I must say, i LOVE Whole Foods, I go there 3x per week for groceries and salads from their salad bar.  I'm not going to anymore now that I've been to this place.  I'd rather be served a nice salad or meal at SweetGreen without the attitude of the Whole Foods staff.  SweetGreen makes you feel like you're stopping in to visit friends.  I like that.  The ONLY thing i will say,  is that their bacon can be quite hard, to the point where i can't even chew it because it hurts my teeth...might want to be careful with that.  Ps. I just read other reviews after i posted mine - not sure what staff were rude to them,  but mine are awesome and i usually go in evenings or towards closing time.
